TEMPORAL

Who takes us to space?

Area Stacked and Stepped

Photo by SpaceX on Unsplash

SpaceX Falcon Heavy

Rockets are cool. There’s no getting around that…
— Elon Musk

REUTERS GRAPHICS created an interesting visual story describing the race for space, its early history dominated by government and military programs, and recent growth into the private sector. The story was also represented with DataWrapper, a visualization platform for data journalism, the example we’ll use to create an area stacked chart.

Ingest the data

series, values, and dates

# Load csv data file
df <- read.csv("archetypes/who-takes-us-to-space/who-takes-us-to-space-long.csv", header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
df

Wrangle the data

Refactor to set stack sort order

# Refactor to set stack sort order
df$SERIES <- factor(df$SERIES, levels = c("Military", "Civil", "Private"))
df

Plot

data only

To created the stepped effect, we’ll use geom_bar() at full width with the same color and fill to create a categorical area shape.

theme_opts <- theme(
    text = element_text(family = "inconsolata"), 
    plot.title = element_text(color = "black", size = 12, face = "bold"),
    plot.subtitle = element_text(color = "black", size = 8),
    plot.caption = element_text(color = "#555555", size = 8),
    axis.title.x = element_blank(),
    axis.title.y = element_blank(),
    # axis.text.x = element_text(vjust = 12),
    panel.border = element_blank(),
    panel.background = element_blank(),
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(), # remove minor gridlines
    panel.grid.major.x = element_blank(), # remove x (vertical) gridlines
    legend.title = element_blank(), # remove legend title
    legend.text = element_text(color = "black", size = 8),
    legend.position='top'
  )

series_pal <- c("Civil" = "#dbdad9",
                "Military" = "#8c92a7",
                "Private" = "#d5b07d")

# Plot
v1 <- ggplot(df, aes(x=DATE, y=VALUE, group = SERIES)) + 
  geom_bar(aes(color = SERIES, fill = SERIES), position="stack", stat="identity", width=1.0) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks=seq(1955,2020, 5)) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks=seq(0, 160, 20)) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = series_pal) +
  scale_color_manual(values = series_pal) +
  labs( title = "Who takes us to space?",
        subtitle = "Reuters Graphics, New Space",
        caption = "") +
  theme_bw() +
  theme_opts

girafe(ggobj = v1, width_svg = 1280/72, height_svg = 720/72,
       options = list(opts_sizing(rescale = TRUE, width = 1.0))
)

Plot with annotations

some narrative to help tell the story

Military launches ushered in the beginning of the space age. They typically carried spy or communication satellites to be used by defense forces.

Civil launches are conducted by government organizations for research purposes. While having accounted for a smaller share of the total launches in history, their number has remained steady.

Private launches are more recent development. These carry payloads to add to the growing number of private and commercial satellites in earth’s orbit, providing imagery and communications services.

v2 <- v1 + 
    annotate("text", x = 1999, y = 90, 
             label = "Cubesat invented", 
             hjust = "center", vjust = 0, color = "#333333", size = 3, fontface = 1, family = "inconsolata") +
    annotate("text", x = 2019, y = 122, 
             label = "Chinese space probe\nlands on dark side\nof the moon", 
             hjust = "right", vjust = 0, color = "#333333", size = 3, fontface = 1, family = "inconsolata") +
    annotate("text", x = 2014, y = 102, 
             label = "India's Mangalyaan\norbiter reaches Mars", 
             hjust = "center", vjust = 0, color = "#333333", size = 3, fontface = 1, family = "inconsolata") +
    annotate("text", x = 1980, y = 139, 
             label = "Develop the Space Shuttle,\nfirst reusable rocket", 
             hjust = "center", vjust = 1, color = "#333333", size = 3, fontface = 1, family = "inconsolata") +
    annotate("text", x = 1958, y = 42, 
             label = "NASA is founded", 
             hjust = "center", vjust = 0, color = "#333333", size = 3, fontface = 1, family = "inconsolata") +
    annotate("text", x = 1957, y = 22, 
             label = "Launch Sputnik\n into orbit", 
             hjust = "center", vjust = 0, color = "#333333", size = 3, fontface = 1, family = "inconsolata") +
    annotate("text", x = 1978, y = 70, 
             label = paste0("During the Cold War,", "\n", "most launches were military."), 
             hjust = "center", vjust = 0, color = "#ffffff", size = 6, fontface = 2, family = "inconsolata") +
    annotate("text", x = 1970, y = 5, 
             label = "Civil", 
             hjust = "center", vjust = 0, color = "#333333", size = 6, fontface = 2, family = "inconsolata") +
    annotate("text", x = 2008, y = 12, 
             label = "Private", 
             hjust = "center", vjust = 0, color = "#333333", size = 6, fontface = 2, family = "inconsolata") +
    theme(legend.position='none')

girafe(ggobj = v2, width_svg = 1280/72, height_svg = 720/72,
       options = list(opts_sizing(rescale = TRUE, width = 1.0))
)
